Probably too late to sneak this in to 2.0.0.

This patch fixes/adds to the GtkSourceView currently non-generated functions. It
allows for the use of the special search feature allowing case insensitive
searching (a built in part of GtkSourceView)

I spent a lot of time on this, ended up rewriting some of the defintions. 
GtkSourceView has a fake type GtkSourceIter, which is /just/ a GtkTextIter, and 
in fact GtkSourceIter is not even in the GtkSourceView code as a type, just the 
documentation. However, it does have gtk_source_iter_forward_search() which when 
bound to a GBoxed of GtkSourceIter breaks *all* GtkTextIter methods. My solution 
to this was to drop _forward_search() and _backward_search() on the main 
GtkSourceView class, in addition to some new flags.

Screenshot:
	http://www.opsat.net/temp/sourceview-search.jpg

Example Code:
	http://p.opsat.net/v/172/54
	(not the best for example)
	(it is a copy paste from the project I am working on but eh)

Added Methods:
	array/bool GtkSourceView::forward_search(
		GtkTreeIter start, string text,
		int flags[, GtkTreeIter stop]
	);
	array/bool GtkSourceView::backward_search(
		GtkTreeIter start, string text,
		int flags[, GtkTreeIter stop]
	);

	Both return array(GtkTreeIter, GtkTreeIter), the start/stop of the match when a 
match is found, and Boolean false when no match was found.

Added Flags:
	GtkSourceView::SEARCH_VISIBLE_ONLY
	GtkSourceView::SEARCH_TEXT_ONLY
	GtkSourceView::SEARCH_CASE_INSENSITIVE



